# npm packages
npm install clinic   # clinic doctor / clinic heapprofiler
npx clinic doctor -- node app.js
```

**Key workflow:** take heap snapshot → do work → take another → compare "retained" objects between snapshots to find what's growing.

CORS errors mean browser blocked request because server didn't permit it.

**Why it happens:** Browser enforces same-origin policy. Request from `a.com` → `b.com` requires `b.com` to explicitly allow it via response headers.

**Common causes:**

| Cause | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Server missing `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header | Add header on server side |
| Preflight (`OPTIONS`) request not handled | Server must respond to `OPTIONS` with correct headers |
| Credentials + wildcard origin | Can't use `*` with `credentials: 'include'` — set explicit origin |
| Wrong port counts as different origin | `localhost:3000` ≠ `localhost:5000` |
| HTTP vs HTTPS mismatch | Protocol is part of origin |

**Quick fixes by backend:**

```js
// Express
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', 'https://yourfrontend.com');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET,POST,PUT,DELETE,OPTIONS');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, Authorization');
  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') return res.sendStatus(204);
  next();
});
```

```python
# FastAPI
from fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware
app.add_middleware(CORSMiddleware, allow_origins=["https://yourfrontend.com"], ...)
```

**Dev shortcut:** Use a proxy in your dev server (`vite.config.js` → `server.proxy`) so requests never cross origins locally.

**Don't fix on frontend** — CORS is enforced by browser, controlled by server. No JS workaround exists (nor should there be).

